attachments.title: Boracay implements stricter penalties against sand thieves
attachments.text: Boracay Island’s legendary powdery white sands may be a tempting souvenir to bring home, but visitors to the famous island should now think twice before doing so. A municipal ordinance has been amended which bans people from collecting white sand and pebbles from the island’s beaches and imposes stricter penalties on those who have been caught doing so.
